title: 'Hounds Trio Statebound from Section 7AA
text:
'Hounds Trio Statebound from Section 7AA 
By Zach Schneider 'Hounds Trio Statebound from Section 7AA October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 6:33 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Duluth East is sending the doubles pairing of Brynne Hauer and Shay Callaway as well as singles player Aili Hietala to the MSHSL Class AA girls' tennis tournament, that after the Section 7AA meet concluded on Monday afternoon. 
Hauer and Callaway beat Princeton's sister pairing of Brianna and Kesley Dorr 6-1, 6-0 on Monday to win the Section 7AA title. The Tigers duo will also advance to state as the section runners-up. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Hietala, meanwhile, lost 6-1, 6-0 in the Section 7AA title match to Elk River's Meagan Brown but will advance to state as the runner-up. 
The individual portion of the MSHSL Class AA girls' tennis tournament starts on Oct. 29 and will be played at the Baseline Tennis Center in Minneapolis, Minn.
